:: Act 3 - Jane Dead - Dawn {"position":"900,1700","size":"100,100"}
Dawn at the strip mall.

Saul Goodman — real name James McGill, age undisclosed, height whatever the shoes say — unlocks Saul Goodman and Associates.

There are no associates.

He flips on the lights. The Statue of Liberty inflatable on the roof hisses awake through the ceiling. He brews what he calls constitutional coffee, which is just the cheapest grounds at the QuikMart run through twice.

He feels the call coming the way old men feel weather.

(click: ?page)[==
The burner has three missed calls from HEISENBERG.
Two from KID.
(click: ?page)[==
He stares at both names for a long time.

### [DECISION 1] — Who do you call back first?

