[[Call the Kid First - Jane Dead]]


:: Call the Kid First - Jane Dead {"position":"750,1850","size":"100,100"}
Voicemail. Of course.

Saul leaves a message in the voice he uses when he's trying to sound calm and isn't:

"Call me back before you call anyone else. That includes nine-one-one. *Especially* nine-one-one. Don't touch anything. Don't talk to anyone. Just — call me back."

(click: ?page)[==
He hangs up and calls Heisenberg.

Walt picks up on the first ring.

*"The girl is dead."*

(click: ?page)[==
Three words. Flat. Like a man reporting weather.

Saul absorbs it the way he absorbs most things — by not absorbing it at all, by filing it immediately into the professional column, by becoming the lawyer in the room even when the room is empty.

(click: ?page)[==
"Go home. Shower. Kiss your wife. Go to work tomorrow. I'll handle the rest."

He hangs up. Calls Mike.

