[[The Mike Call - Jane Dead]]


:: The Mike Call - Jane Dead {"position":"900,2000","size":"100,100"}
Thirty seconds flat.

Address. Apartment number. Specific situation.

Mike doesn't do small talk.

"The kid in the apartment too?"

(click: ?page)[==
Saul hears what's inside the question. He knows Mike well enough to know Mike isn't asking because he wants to hurt anyone. He's asking because Mike is thorough and thorough means accounting for all the variables.

But still.

"Do NOT touch the kid."

"I'm not going to touch the kid, Saul."

(click: ?page)[==
Mike hangs up. Saul realizes his hand is shaking on the receiver.

He didn't actually think Mike would. But he had to say it anyway.

That small moment — the fact that he had to say it — is the first crack in the armor this morning.

(click: ?page)[==
Hours pass. Saul doesn't leave the office.

He watches the Statue of Liberty inflate and deflate through the window. He thinks about how he got here. Not this morning — here. How every small professional compromise lines up behind you like cars on a highway until you can't see where the road started.

The burner rings. It's the Kid.

[[Jesse Calls - Jane Dead]]


:: Jesse Calls - Jane Dead {"position":"900,2150","size":"100,100"}
Jesse is crying so hard Saul can't understand him for thirty seconds.

He's trying to say something about Jane. He's trying to say something about waking up and she was just —

"I know," Saul says. "I already know. Listen to me. There's a guy coming to take care of everything. Everything, okay? His name doesn't matter. He's going to make this look like what it is — an overdose. Because it *was* an overdose."

(click: ?page)[==
Jesse starts to ask *did Mr. White —*

"Motel. East side. Now. I'll come to you."

Jesse goes quiet. Then: "Okay."

(click: ?page)[==
Saul sits in the car outside the motel for four minutes before going in.

He tells himself he's thinking about what to say. He isn't. He's stalling. He's been stalling his whole career.

[[The Motel Room - Jane Dead]]


:: The Motel Room - Jane Dead {"position":"900,2300","size":"100,100"}
Jesse is sitting on the edge of the bed with his hands clasped between his knees.

For one second he looks like a kid sent to the principal's office.

Then Saul looks at his face again and it's nothing like that. It's grief so raw it hasn't found a shape yet.

Saul pulls up the one chair. They sit in silence.

(click: ?page)[==
Then Jesse says, very quietly:

*"I think I killed her."*

(click: ?page)[==
Saul sees his two options with perfect clarity.

He can tell Jesse what he suspects. That Walt was there. That Walt let it happen — or helped it happen — or at minimum stood there and did nothing while a girl choked to death because she was inconvenient.

Or he can let Jesse carry it.

Easier. Cleaner. Better for the operation. Better for the retainer.

(click: ?page)[==
Jesse is staring at the carpet.

### [DECISION 2] — What do you tell him?

[[Let Jesse Believe It - Jane Dead]]
[[Tell Jesse the Truth - Jane Dead]]


:: Let Jesse Believe It - Jane Dead {"position":"700,2475","size":"100,100"}
Saul goes into professional mode like flipping a switch.

"Addicts die, Jesse. It's what happens. She rolled the wrong way. You couldn't have known. You couldn't have stopped it."

(click: ?page)[==
Jesse nods. He isn't really hearing the words. He's hearing the permission to hate himself, and that's what he wanted — something that makes the grief make sense by giving it an address.

Saul watches it settle on him like a coat.

(click: ?page)[==
"I know a place," Saul says. "Past Los Lunas. Takes cash, no questions. You go in, you get clean, you come out the other side."

Jesse doesn't say anything for a long time.

"...okay."

(click: ?page)[==
In the parking lot, Saul stands next to his car for a full minute before getting in.

He did the professional thing. Kept the client alive. Kept the operation intact. Kept the retainer on the desk.

He also just watched a kid take the weight of something that wasn't his, and handed him the straps himself.

He gets in the car.

[[Saul's Decision - Bad Path]]


:: Tell Jesse the Truth - Jane Dead {"position":"1100,2475","size":"100,100"}
Saul opens his mouth.

Closes it.

Opens it again.

This is going to violate approximately nine bar association rules and his own rule number one, which is *do not get involved*, and which he has never once successfully followed in thirty years of practice.

(click: ?page)[==
"I don't think you killed her."

Jesse looks up.

"I think somebody was there. Somebody who knew she was a problem. Somebody who called me that morning *already knowing* she was dead."

(click: ?page)[==
Jesse's face does the math slowly. Then all at once.

"No."

Saul gives him the silence.

Jesse stares at the wall. His jaw is tight. His hands are shaking.

After a long time: "Why are you telling me this?"

(click: ?page)[==
Saul surprises himself with the answer.

"Because I've been on the other side of this my whole career. I'm the guy who talks people into eating it. And I am very tired. You deserve to know what you're walking out of."

(click: ?page)[==
Jesse doesn't say anything. He doesn't have to.

### [DECISION 3] — What do you tell Jesse to do?

[[Get Jesse Out - Jane Dead Good Ending]]
[[Leave Jesse to His Choices - Jane Dead Bad Ending]]


:: Get Jesse Out - Jane Dead Good Ending {"position":"1100,2650","size":"100,100"}
"I know a guy," Saul says. "Not the rehab kind. The disappearing kind. New name, new state. You drive north and you don't come back."

(click: ?page)[==
Jesse stares at the carpet.

"Alaska," he says finally.

"Sure. Alaska. Why not Alaska."

(click: ?page)[==
Two weeks later, Saul drives Jesse to a pull-off past the city limits where a plain white van is idling. Jesse gets out with a backpack and nothing else.

He doesn't hug Saul. Doesn't say thank you. Doesn't say anything.

He nods once.

Saul nods back.

The van drives north.

(click: ?page)[==
Saul stands in the dust until the taillights are gone.

When he gets back to the office, Heisenberg is going to call. Walt is going to ask where his partner went. Saul is going to lie to his face.

For the first time in a long time, he's going to sleep fine that night.

(click: ?page)[==
---

*Jesse Pinkman drove north and kept driving.*

*He changed his name. He learned to work with his hands. He built things.*

*He never cooked again.*

