:: Jesse Calls - Jane Alive {"position":"300,1875","size":"100,100"}
"Yo, it's me."

"I know it's you. What's happening?"

"Jane's alive." 

A pause. Like Jesse is still surprised by it.

"She's okay. She was — it was bad, but she's okay. And Saul, I think Mr. White was there. I think he was in the apartment."

(click: ?page)[==
Saul is quiet for a moment.

"What makes you think that?"

"Because she told me. She woke up and she — she says she saw him. Standing there. Just standing there."

(click: ?page)[==
Another pause on the line. Longer this time.

"And then she said he reached down and rolled her over."

(click: ?page)[==
Saul stares at the Statue of Liberty through the window.

*He reached down and rolled her over.*

After everything. After all the inches Walt has been sliding in one direction, he stopped at the last one.

Saul doesn't know what to do with that. He files it. He'll figure it out later.

"Come to the office. Bring Jane. Don't call Walt yet."

[[The Office Meeting - Jane Alive]]


