Walt sits at the kitchen table for three hours after Jesse leaves.

Skyler is at work. Flynn is at school. The house is the quietest place on earth.

He thinks about Jesse. About the girl. About the moment in that apartment when his hand stopped in the air and then kept moving anyway, and what that means about who he still is, somewhere underneath everything he's become.

